On the night of the crime, guard Lei Jie acted suspiciously

21
00:01:15,219 --> 00:01:18,200
They decide to check out Lei Jie's place for a clue

22
00:01:20,219 --> 00:01:22,200
The Illumin-Eye

23
00:01:37,219 --> 00:01:38,640
Huh?

24
00:01:42,640 --> 00:01:44,200
I don't remember seeing this juice box last time I came

25
00:01:44,200 --> 00:01:45,439
Ah, juice!

26
00:01:48,439 --> 00:01:48,980
What the heck? [DVD: Dead Chicken]

27
00:01:48,980 --> 00:01:50,239
This isn't juice!

28
00:01:50,239 --> 00:01:54,340
I've been looking for this movie forever.

29
00:01:54,340 --> 00:01:55,620
Never thought I'd find it here—ha!

30
00:01:59,219 --> 00:02:00,980
It's starting, it's starting, it's starting!

31
00:02:00,980 --> 00:02:05,659
Hello, dear viewers~

32
00:02:05,659 --> 00:02:07,439
What's this nonsense?

33
00:02:07,439 --> 00:02:08,939
It's Smile Match!

34
00:02:08,939 --> 00:02:10,039
And it's from the day before yesterday!

35
00:02:10,039 --> 00:02:13,300
Are you sure this is from the day before yesterday?

36
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:15,219
Of course!

37
00:02:15,219 --> 00:02:16,659
I watch it on time every day.

38
00:02:16,659 --> 00:02:19,579
What time does this show air daily?

39
00:02:19,579 --> 00:02:22,139
Are you from Mars?

40
00:02:22,139 --> 00:02:23,219
A show this popular,

41
00:02:23,219 --> 00:02:24,979
and you don't know its airtime?

42
00:02:24,979 --> 00:02:27,759
It's 11:30 PM every day, of course!

43
00:02:27,759 --> 00:02:30,699
Let's go talk to the apartment manager.

44
00:02:30,699 --> 00:02:35,780
Excuse me, do you know Lei Jie who lives here?

45
00:02:35,780 --> 00:02:36,359
Lei Jie?

46
00:02:36,359 --> 00:02:37,340
Of course I do.

47
00:02:37,340 --> 00:02:38,780
That guy has no hygiene—

48
00:02:38,780 --> 00:02:41,099
he tosses trash anywhere, and won't listen to warnings.

49
00:02:41,099 --> 00:02:43,239
Do you remember the night before last,

50
00:02:43,239 --> 00:02:46,239
after the 11 PM curfew, Lei Jie came back?

51
00:02:46,239 --> 00:02:47,399
And even got scolded by you.

52
00:02:47,399 --> 00:02:49,840
Every day when he comes back, I tell him—

53
00:02:49,840 --> 00:02:51,299
Take out the trash!

54
00:02:51,299 --> 00:02:52,919
But he just won’t listen.

55
00:02:52,919 --> 00:02:56,439
Also, our building is open 24 hours.

56
00:02:56,439 --> 00:02:57,599
Where’s the curfew?

57
00:02:57,599 --> 00:03:01,400
The night before last, Lei Jie brought this foreigner back around eight.

58
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:04,340
Then he ran out again and didn’t come back till dawn.

59
00:03:04,340 --> 00:03:06,019
No idea what he was up to.

60
00:03:06,019 --> 00:03:08,759
How does that match Mr. K’s timeline at all?

61
00:03:08,759 --> 00:03:13,180
I already know who the culprit is.

62
00:03:13,180 --> 00:03:14,439
Let’s talk back at the station.

63
00:03:14,439 --> 00:03:16,259
Thanks for the tip.

64
00:03:16,259 --> 00:03:17,299
Mister in charge.

65
00:03:17,299 --> 00:03:18,099
Bye-bye.

66
00:03:27,599 --> 00:03:35,359
Hello, who’s this?

67
00:03:35,359 --> 00:03:37,699
Hey, I’ve already been spotted by that little detective.

68
00:03:37,699 --> 00:03:39,240
Pay me the rest of the money now.

69
00:03:39,240 --> 00:03:40,459
I need to lay low.

70
00:03:40,459 --> 00:03:43,199
Lei Jie, you’re too naive.

71
00:03:43,199 --> 00:03:45,120
You were just a pawn.

72
00:03:45,120 --> 00:03:47,979
Now you’re of no use anymore.

73
00:03:47,979 --> 00:03:48,879
You jerk.

74
00:03:48,879 --> 00:03:50,159
How dare you treat me like this?

75
00:03:50,159 --> 00:03:51,139
You’re the one who ordered me.

76
00:03:51,139 --> 00:03:52,919
Aren't you afraid I'll rat you out?

77
00:03:52,919 --> 00:03:56,479
Haha~ Right now, all the evidence points to

78
00:03:56,480 --> 00:03:57,680
you being the criminal.

79
00:03:57,680 --> 00:04:00,680
And you're the only one who actually stole the gem.

80
00:04:00,680 --> 00:04:02,680
Who'd believe your story?

81
00:04:03,680 --> 00:04:04,680
Hahahahaha!

82
00:04:07,280 --> 00:04:09,280
Mr. Lei Jie, in a fine mood,

83
00:04:11,680 --> 00:04:14,680
enjoying the sunset all alone, are we?

84
00:04:15,080 --> 00:04:15,680
Go!

85
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:21,879
You looking for me?

86
00:04:22,280 --> 00:04:23,480
The one who used the invisibility watch

87
00:04:23,480 --> 00:04:25,280
to steal the gem, Angel's Tears,

88
00:04:25,280 --> 00:04:26,720
is you.

89
00:04:26,720 --> 00:04:29,160
Haha, absurd, absurd!

90
00:04:29,160 --> 00:04:30,980
When the crime happened, I was with Mr. K.

91
00:04:30,980 --> 00:04:31,860
I have a witness!

92
00:04:31,860 --> 00:04:34,680
You got Mr. K drunk first,

93
00:04:34,680 --> 00:04:36,020
then helped him back to your apartment.

94
00:04:36,020 --> 00:04:37,920
The strange accent of the apartment manager's scolding

95
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:39,300
was explained by you as a curfew warning,

96
00:04:39,300 --> 00:04:40,480
to give the drunken Mr. K

97
00:04:40,480 --> 00:04:42,160
the impression it was already late.

98
00:04:42,160 --> 00:04:42,940
But in reality,

99
00:04:42,940 --> 00:04:43,600
the actual time

100
00:04:43,600 --> 00:04:45,700
was still far from 23:00.

101
00:04:48,700 --> 00:04:49,600
Don't forget—

102
00:04:49,600 --> 00:04:50,620
At 11:30 PM,

103
00:04:50,620 --> 00:04:51,600
I was with Mr. K,

104
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:52,500
watching TV at home.

105
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:54,080
Hmph. You waited until Mr. K

106
00:04:54,080 --> 00:04:55,140
fell asleep in your bed,

107
00:04:55,139 --> 00:04:56,719
used the VCR's auto-record function

108
00:04:56,719 --> 00:04:58,379
to tape the TV show,

109
00:04:58,379 --> 00:05:00,240
then stole Mr. K's keys

110
00:05:00,240 --> 00:05:02,860
and robbed the museum between 11:30 and midnight.

111
00:05:02,860 --> 00:05:04,500
When you got back early morning,

112
00:05:04,500 --> 00:05:05,819
you played the pre-recorded

113
00:05:05,819 --> 00:05:07,259
Smile Match on the TV,

114
00:05:07,259 --> 00:05:09,180
then woke up a groggy Mr. K,

115
00:05:09,180 --> 00:05:10,300
handed him a hangover pill,

116
00:05:10,300 --> 00:05:12,599
and faked being home the whole time.

117
00:05:12,599 --> 00:05:15,240
But you overlooked the apartment manager—

118
00:05:15,240 --> 00:05:18,159
because of your hygiene issues,

119
00:05:18,159 --> 00:05:20,539
he remembered your comings and goings clearly.

120
00:05:20,539 --> 00:05:22,899
And your fake alibi

121
00:05:22,899 --> 00:05:24,419
along with the forgotten tape

122
00:05:24,420 --> 00:05:27,420
became your Achilles' heel!

123
00:05:37,420 --> 00:05:40,420
I only stole to support my family.

124
00:05:41,420 --> 00:05:43,420
Was I really wrong?

125
00:05:43,420 --> 00:05:46,420
Was I... really wrong?

126
00:05:46,420 --> 00:05:49,420
Aaaahhh!

127
00:05:53,420 --> 00:05:55,420
I was blind to trust

128
00:05:55,420 --> 00:05:58,420
that venomous snake I worked for—!!

129
00:06:00,420 --> 00:06:01,420
After him!

130
00:06:11,420 --> 00:06:13,420
Ah! He's fast.

131
00:06:13,420 --> 00:06:15,420
Didn't expect him to be so agile.

132
00:06:15,420 --> 00:06:16,420
Captain, don't rush.

133
00:06:16,420 --> 00:06:18,420
Even if it costs me everything,

134
00:06:18,420 --> 00:06:20,420
I, Sima Gang, will bring that crook to justice.

135
00:06:20,420 --> 00:06:22,420
For the people's sake.

136
00:06:27,420 --> 00:06:29,420
Right on time.

137
00:06:34,420 --> 00:06:35,420
You—

138
00:06:40,420 --> 00:06:42,420
Trying to run after being exposed?

139
00:06:48,420 --> 00:06:49,420
Move aside!

140
00:06:49,420 --> 00:06:51,420
Hehe, no way.

141
00:06:51,420 --> 00:06:53,420
You're asking for it.

142
00:06:54,420 --> 00:06:56,420
[XX-rated scene—viewers under 18 not allowed]

143
00:06:59,420 --> 00:07:01,420
Still trying to run?

144
00:07:01,420 --> 00:07:02,420
Uncle!

145
00:07:02,420 --> 00:07:04,420
Great, Detective Chen.

146
00:07:04,420 --> 00:07:05,420
Lei Jie.

147
00:07:05,420 --> 00:07:07,420
As a security officer, you stole from your own post.

148
00:07:07,420 --> 00:07:08,420
I'm arresting you now.

149
00:07:08,420 --> 00:07:10,420
Anything to say for yourself?

150
00:07:13,420 --> 00:07:14,420
Caught by you.

151
00:07:14,420 --> 00:07:15,220
Just my luck.

152
00:07:15,220 --> 00:07:16,720
But I was set up by someone.

153
00:07:17,319 --> 00:07:19,420
He used me and then threw me under the bus.

154
00:07:19,420 --> 00:07:21,220
I'm gonna rat him out.

155
00:07:21,220 --> 00:07:23,620
The real mastermind is...

156
00:07:24,420 --> 00:07:26,420
Mr. K.

157
00:07:28,920 --> 00:07:31,220
About a week ago,

158
00:07:31,920 --> 00:07:35,220
Mr. K was transporting gems to the museum for an exhibition.

159
00:07:35,620 --> 00:07:38,819
Secretly, he bribed me heavily to steal the gems,

160
00:07:39,120 --> 00:07:42,020
promising I'd get away clean.

161
00:07:42,019 --> 00:07:46,279
Back then, I was blinded by greed and agreed without a second thought.

162
00:07:46,279 --> 00:07:47,359
On the night of the heist,

163
00:07:47,359 --> 00:07:49,719
he said we'd hit a bar to celebrate early.

164
00:07:49,719 --> 00:07:52,680
Then he insisted on checking out my apartment.

165
00:07:52,680 --> 00:07:54,039
At the apartment entrance,

166
00:07:54,039 --> 00:07:55,599
I got chewed out by the building manager

167
00:07:55,599 --> 00:07:57,759
over some hygiene issues.

168
00:07:57,759 --> 00:08:00,680
Mr. K seemed pretty intrigued by that.

169
00:08:00,680 --> 00:08:01,939
Back in the apartment,

170
00:08:01,939 --> 00:08:04,659
he handed me the invisibility watch and the vault key,

171
00:08:04,659 --> 00:08:07,459
telling me to pull the heist at exactly 11:30 PM.

172
00:08:07,459 --> 00:08:08,959
When I got back,

173
00:08:08,959 --> 00:08:11,560
I found him recording the Smile Match show.

174
00:08:11,560 --> 00:08:14,439
He said he was really into the show

175
00:08:14,439 --> 00:08:17,360
and told me to keep the tape safe.

176
00:08:17,360 --> 00:08:20,040
Give it to him after he leaves.

177
00:08:20,040 --> 00:08:22,860
But I never imagined...

178
00:08:22,860 --> 00:08:27,079
All of this was carefully planned by him—

179
00:08:27,079 --> 00:08:27,720
A trap!

180
00:08:27,720 --> 00:08:29,699
See? See?

181
00:08:29,699 --> 00:08:31,139
I suspected Mr. K all along.

182
00:08:31,139 --> 00:08:32,500
You guys just didn't believe me.

183
00:08:32,500 --> 00:08:34,600
Did Mr. K ever tell you

184
00:08:34,600 --> 00:08:36,399
what his purpose was for stealing the gem?

185
00:08:36,399 --> 00:08:39,059
I overheard him contacting someone.

186
00:08:39,059 --> 00:08:40,600
Sounded like a deal.

187
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:42,060
The meeting place was...

188
00:08:47,060 --> 00:08:48,659
There's a light!

189
00:08:48,659 --> 00:08:53,240
It's Mr. K.

190
00:08:53,240 --> 00:08:57,159
Almost ruined by this idiot.

191
00:08:57,159 --> 00:08:59,879
So you really are the mastermind.

192
00:08:59,879 --> 00:09:01,940
Better surrender quietly now.

193
00:09:01,940 --> 00:09:04,940
Catching me won't be that easy.

194
00:09:04,940 --> 00:09:10,580
Take our 'Love and Ideals'

195
00:09:10,580 --> 00:09:13,820
and soar freely in the sky!

196
00:09:13,820 --> 00:09:16,420
The big villain is getting away!

197
00:09:16,420 --> 00:09:17,780
Open fire!

198
00:09:17,780 --> 00:09:24,480
Obstructing the Illumin-Eye's sacred plan—

199
00:09:24,480 --> 00:09:27,280
you will pay the price!

200
00:09:27,280 --> 00:09:31,620
You're a big, bad villain! A big, bad villain!

201
00:09:31,620 --> 00:09:33,720
Big bad guy, big bad guy

202
00:09:33,720 --> 00:09:39,060
Is it The Illumin-Eye?

203
00:10:03,720 --> 00:10:33,700
Subtitle Volunteer: Yang Xixi

204
00:10:33,720 --> 00:11:03,700
